ðŸ§± Basic Data Types in Python : 

1. Integers (int) :
Basically they are whole numbers positive or negative, no decimals .
Ex : 1 4 7 -200 80 
Python code exemple :

x = 996
y = 43

2. Floating Point Numbers (float) :
Numbers with decimal points .
EX : 23,455  / 9,066374
Python code exemple : 

x = 4.34
y = 377.88935

3. Strings (str) :
A sequence of characters enclosed in quotes " " .
Python code exemple : 

name = "Alice" 
greeting = "Hello" 

4. Booleans (bool) :
Logical values : True or false .
Pyhton code exemple : 

is_active = True 
has_permission = False 



Those are the basic Data types in python , i know there are more but i will go slowly step by step to discover all of them later in my journey .


